#Approach:

Approach:
Ye code circular array ka Next Greater Element nikalne ke liye monotonic decreasing stack use karta hai.

1. Normal NGE me hum right se left ek baar traverse karte hain,
   lekin yahan array circular hai, isliye 2*n - 1 se 0 tak traverse kiya gaya hai.
2. हर step par current element nums[i % n] liya jaata hai,
   jisse array circularly access ho jaye.
3. Stack se current se chhote ya equal elements pop kar dete hain,
   kyuki wo next greater nahi ban sakte.
4. Jab i < n hota hai tab actual answer fill karte hain:
   - stack empty ho to -1
   - warna stack top hi next greater hai
5. Fir current element ko stack me push kar dete hain.

Main idea:
Array ko 2 baar traverse karke circular behavior simulate kiya gaya hai.
Stack hamesha possible next greater elements ko maintain karta hai.

Time Complexity: O(n)
Space Complexity: O(n)

#Code:

class Solution {
    public int[] nextGreaterElements(int[] nums) {
        Deque<Integer> stack = new ArrayDeque<>();
        int n = nums.length;
        int[] nge = new int[n];

        for(int i=(2*n)-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(!stack.isEmpty() && stack.peek() <= nums[i%n]){
                stack.pop();
            }

            if(i<n){
                nge[i] = stack.isEmpty() ? -1 : stack.peek();
            }
            stack.push(nums[i%n]);
        }
        return nge;
    }
}
